VChakri&#8217;s lilting tunes
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe musical nite conducted by film music director Chakri at SV University stadium in Tirupati last Saturday turned out to be a mega hit, with the impressive crowd matching the stirring live performance. The songs were pre-recorded in the Karaoke form\u000aat before the show, while Chakri&#8217;s team lent its voice to give a scintillating performance. There was a thunderous response from the youth to his fast numbers likeAlale Alale&#8230; from the movieItlu Sravani SubramanyamandChoopultho Guchi GuchifromIdiot, while the melodious onesRama Rama Rama&#8230;fromShivamani,Jagamantha Kutumbam NaadifromChakramandRaa Rammani&#8230; fromAvunu Valliddaru Ishtapaddarutoo received great applause. The latest songsGo Go&#8230;andNuvvakkaduntefrom his recent hit filmGopi Gopika Godavaritoo were a rage with youngsters.The event was a charity show and the proceeds were meant for the inmates of Abhaya Kshetram, a home for differently-abled children in Tirupati. Chakri lauded the efforts of the Kshetram&#8217;s founder S.A. Thasleem, a doctorate holder in Special Education, for focusing on the betterment of the lives of children. The cultural programmes by the special children of Abhaya Kshetram attracted one and all.
